  "body": "Hi all,\r\n\r\nCurrently, our beacon node always starts from a genesis timestamp of time.Now() which causes the system to start from slot 0 (being genesis), 1, 2, 3, ...\r\n\r\nThe problem is that if data is persisted (i.e. a block is determined as canonical), restarting the node will fail as the system will detect slot 0 to be time.Now() even though there exists a canonical head from the past. a PR to resolve this will set the genesis time of the system to be time.Now() if no data has been persisted. Otherwise, it will set it to the timestamp of the genesis block from persistent storage.",
